Setting Webhook

Install the necessary plugins: GitHub Integration

Configure Jenkins Project:

Open your Jenkins project.

Click on "Configure" in the left-hand menu.

Under the "Build Triggers" section, check the box for "GitHub hook trigger for GITScm polling" 

 

Set Up Webhook in Version Control System (GitHub):

Go to GitHub repository.
Click on "Settings."
Choose "Webhooks" from the menu on the left.
Click "Add webhook" and provide the Jenkins server URL with the appropriate path (e.g., http://your-jenkins-server/github-webhook/).


Select the events that should trigger the webhook.
Add the webhook.
